data.title: Great food!
data.text: The food was great as alway, they were busy but that got our Apps and food out in fast order! Would come here again.

data.title: Excellent food, good service!
data.text:
We stopped in here before seeing a play at the Duluth Playhouse.  

The food is excellent and the service is good.  It's a very busy place, and the wait staff really hustled in between tables to keep up, but took their time at each table to greet and treat their customers well.

My wife and I shared a pizza and some cheese garlic bread.  Both were very good.  The crust and sauce on the pizza were great, and the the cheese was just right...not too little, but not so much that it was overwhelming to the rest of the pizza and ingredients.

data.title: Very dissapointing veggie pizza
data.text:
We stopped over for dinner on our way back from lutsen. Searched tripadvisor to find this pizza joint, we were seriously dissapointed with the food.

We wanted a veggie option hence went for the fehttuchini alfredo, fehttuchini pesto and a veggie pizza.

The only thing which was served OK was the fehttuchini alfredo. The Fehttuchini pesto had way too much pesto and basil, so much that it was giving a bitter after taste. (we had tried this in noddle company and its way better)

VEggie piizza was made by some noob, probably who has never baked a pizza before. There were just olives, just green and black olives, so much that you cannot feel anything else. The marinara was overdone and it was adding to the already tangy taste thanks to the olives.

I mean how difficult is a veggie pizza, i can make a better veggie pizza than this. this place has got good ratings, probably has experienced chefs making the other pizzas with meat options.

My advice would be if you are looking for a veggie pizza, this is definitely not a place to go.

Our server was good and the service was pretty fast, even our server acknowledge that the chef is new and thanked us for our feedback. Hence the two stars.

Sammy's Pizza, your server was great, apart from that there was nothing there for us, worst pizza ever.

Oh i forgot, who puts raw tomatoes on top of a pizza, like a dressing..There are sundried tomatoes but they all go into the oven not dressed up like toppings of a salad.

data.title: Great old-style, thin crust pizza
data.text: This place was a block away from the motel I was staying at, so I called for carryout.  It was hot and ready on time.  The staff were all friendly and thankful when I arrived. They gave me extra hot peppers, parmesan cheese, and napkins. The pizza was a delicious cracker-style thin crust.  I ordered "The Crew" special: Sausage, pepperoni, mushroom, and extra cheese.  It was PERFECT.  I'm sure there are plenty of good pizzas in Duluth, but I may never know about them. I'll be coming back for this one.

data.title: Good food, horrible service
data.text:
We went here after a cross country meet today.  When we first arrived, no one else was in the restaurant...waited forever to get someone to wait on us, food came out quickly once the order was in and the food was very good.  When it came time for the bill...we had to wait again because the waiter only wanted to service the large group in the other room.  

Verdict:  Good food, but stick to take out or try another location.

data.title: Expensive Wine
data.text: A casual place to go with our family for pizza. Nice choices of pizzas and a children's menu. The pizza was very good and I had a glass of house chardonnay. You can imagine how surprised I was when we got our bill that this little glass of wine cost over $8.00 after tax. This is a pizza joint not "Mustards" in Napa Valley. Wow!!

data.title: Great Thin Crust Pizza
data.text: I always stop in for Pizza when I am in Duluth. Some of the best thin crust pizza I have ever had. Great for families, sports teams. I have done all of that here. Reasonably priced and good service. Definitely the best pizza in Duluth.

data.title: Good not great
data.text: Good pizza. Being from new Haven I consider myself a Hardcore pizza snob but I don't doubt this is the best pizza in Duluth. Sauce was good and generous with toppings however I did notice the toppings tend to slide off the pizza crust.

data.title: Delicious Pizza!
data.text: We went to the Lakeside Sammy's pizza and had the "House Special Pizza".  The crust was a real Italian one. There were tons of toppings and no shortage of cheese. Loved it!

data.title: Wasn't so good this time.
data.text: We have been eating Sammy's Pizza since we were in high school. It was in Superior then and closed a few years ago but is in the process of reopening.This time, it wasn't so good. We ordered half Cheeseburger, half pepperoni and it just wasn't tasty.

data.title: Great Pizza with Great Service
data.text: We had a delicious lunch here.  Ordered a simple five cheese pizza and it was amazing.  Service was fast and friendly.

data.title: Great food...looks run down
data.text: We've eaten at Sammy's throughout MN and ND for over 40 years.  The food quality is always consistent and delicious.  This restaurant looks run down and really needs a facelift.

data.title: Fed Ex Extra Large ASAP
data.text:
If you enjoy thin crust pizza with pinched
edges, a family sauce and nice toppings.....,,,!??? You'll get when you question yourself for eating it 3 days in a row.   Not all Sammys are the same but the downtown Duluth location is top notch with Finnish Vinny leading the parade.

data.title: Classic thin crust pizza!
data.text: We stopped in on a rainy Saturday night around 8 p.m.  The dining room was very quiet so we had excellent service.  The kitchen was busy fulfilling take out or delivery orders but our order arrived quickly.  The best menu item we tried was the garlic cheese bread.  We ordered a whole and we gobbled it up.  We ordered a large cheese and a large veggie (with pepperoni hahaha).  Both were delicious, hand made thin crust, high quality ingredients.  We will return when in Duluth.

data.title: The best pizza around
data.text: Sammy's has been a place to get great pizza since the 60's for me . When I go back to Duluth this is a must stop!!

data.title: After 40 years, I still love it!
data.text:
I've been a patron of Sammy's since high school, when we would sit in the back booths and share pizza if we could find some change!

it is still my top choice for pizza.  The crust is homemade, unlike many of the chain pizzas, the sauce is excellent, and the toppings generous.  I love the thin crust.

data.title: Yumm!
data.text:
I had the Chicken Bacon Ranch pizza delivered to my hotel room and thought the pizza was delicious.  There was the perfect amount of sauce on the pizza that it didn't taste dry.  The delivery person was very friendly.

I did have an issue with the website and calling in my order as I was unaware of the variety of sizes Sammy's offered and the person taking my order appeared slightly irritated by this.

Overall very good food and would order from them again.

data.title: A Family Tradition
data.text: Sammy's Pizza in Duluth MN has been a family gathering spot for over 50 years. We think it's the BEST pizza around.

data.title: Fantastic
data.text: This pizza reminded me of a pizza I grew up with decades ago ... I found this place by accident while on business. . . Service was excellent, and the pizza came out piping hot and tasted fantastic !!! ... Will definitely return if business takes me back. You just can't go wrong.

data.title: YUM!
data.text: Such good food. It was our first time and will be back for sure! Food was deliver hot and authentic! I called them to tell them how impressed I was!
